// 03a-data-nmr-databases — NMR Spectral Databases

The foundation of any data-driven approach to NMR-based property prediction is a large, structurally diverse corpus of molecular NMR spectra paired with unambiguous chemical identifiers. This section surveys the fourteen NMR spectral databases evaluated for this work, ranging from million-scale text-mined collections to small, expertly curated reference libraries. @tab-nmr-databases provides a summary of all databases considered, including their scale, data format, and access method. The databases span a wide range of provenance: some contain exclusively experimental measurements, others provide computationally predicted spectra, and several offer both. They also differ dramatically in data representation, from raw free induction decays (FIDs) to processed peak lists to bucketed pseudo-spectra, and in accessibility, from fully open REST APIs to Cloudflare-protected web interfaces with no programmatic access whatsoever.

